### ============================================================================
### TOOGLE MASTER - API REQUESTS
### ============================================================================
### Este arquivo pode ser usado com a extensão "REST Client" no VS Code
### ou no WebStorm para testar as APIs localmente.
### ============================================================================

@auth_host = http://localhost:8001
@flag_host = http://localhost:8002
@targeting_host = http://localhost:8003
@evaluation_host = http://localhost:8004
@analytics_host = http://localhost:8005

# Substitua pelas chaves reais após cria-las
@master_key = sua_chave_mestra_aqui
@api_key = tm_key_fe9f3db5d2d3e40dc2bbb753ed1c50a12da0677a9a58e26d983a3bd0c5ea30b0

### ============================================================================
### 1. AUTH SERVICE (Porta 8001)
### ============================================================================

### 1.1. Health Check
GET {{auth_host}}/health

### 1.2. Criar nova chave de API (Requer MASTER_KEY)
# @name createKey
POST {{auth_host}}/admin/keys
Authorization: Bearer {{master_key}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Chave do Flag Service"
}

### 1.3. Validar chave de API
GET {{auth_host}}/validate
Authorization: Bearer {{api_key}}


### ============================================================================
### 2. FLAG SERVICE (Porta 8002)
### ============================================================================

### 2.1. Health Check
GET {{flag_host}}/health

### 2.2. Criar uma nova Flag (Requer API KEY válida)
POST {{flag_host}}/flags
Authorization: Bearer {{api_key}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "testenovo3",
    "description": "Ativa o novo fluxo de checkout",
    "is_enabled": true
}

### 2.3. Listar todas as Flags
GET {{flag_host}}/flags
Authorization: Bearer {{api_key}}

### 2.4. Buscar uma Flag específica
GET {{flag_host}}/flags/testenovo
Authorization: Bearer {{api_key}}


### ============================================================================
### 3. TARGETING SERVICE (Porta 8003)
### ============================================================================

### 3.1. Health Check
GET {{targeting_host}}/health

### 3.2. Criar uma regra para uma Flag
POST {{targeting_host}}/rules
Authorization: Bearer {{api_key}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "flag_name": "testenovo3",
    "is_enabled": true,
    "rules": {
        "type": "PERCENTAGE",
        "value": 90.0
    }
}

### 3.3. Buscar regra de uma Flag
GET {{targeting_host}}/rules/new_checkout_flow
Authorization: Bearer {{api_key}}


### ============================================================================
### 4. EVALUATION SERVICE (Porta 8004)
### ============================================================================

### 4.1. Health Check
GET {{evaluation_host}}/health

### 4.2. Avaliar uma Flag para um Usuário (Requer API KEY válida)
# O Evaluation precisa se comunicar com Redis, Flag e Targeting para responder
GET {{evaluation_host}}/evaluate?flag_name=new_checkout_flow&user_id=user_12345
Authorization: Bearer {{api_key}}


### ============================================================================
### 5. ANALYTICS SERVICE (Porta 8005)
### ============================================================================

### 5.1. Health Check
# Nota: O Analytics Service processa mensagens do SQS em background.
# O endpoint HTTP serve apenas para health check.
GET {{analytics_host}}/health
